Currently in JIRA database [Workflow schemes|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/JIRA/Configuring+workflow+schemes?src=search] refer to [Workflows|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/JIRA/Configuring+Workflow] by the Workflow name, this can cause problems as the one described in this [KB|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/JIRAKB/JIRA+Crashes+and+Throws+%27Unknown+workflow+name%27+Error].
{code}
mysql> select * from workflowschemeentity;
+-------+--------+---------------------------------------------+-----------+
| ID    | SCHEME | WORKFLOW                                    | issuetype |
+-------+--------+---------------------------------------------+-----------+
| 10000 |  10000 | Agile Simplified Workflow for Project TSTII | 0         |
+-------+--------+---------------------------------------------+-----------+
1 row in set (0.00 sec)
{code}
{code}
mysql> select ID, workflowname, creatorname, ISLOCKED from jiraworkflows;
+-------+---------------------------------------------+-------------+----------+
| ID    | workflowname                                | creatorname | ISLOCKED |
+-------+---------------------------------------------+-------------+----------+
| 10000 | Agile Simplified Workflow for Project TSTII | NULL        | NULL     |
+-------+---------------------------------------------+-------------+----------+
1 row in set (0.00 sec)
{code}

Many problems and inconsistencies can be avoided if the Workflow schemes refer to Workflows ID, instead of the Workflow name.

