While we have a setting in JIRA that limits the amount of characters a comment can contain this is not always fail proof ( IE comments by email, preexisting comments before the setting was in place, etc ) leading to comments that are 1 megabyte and above in size.

This becomes problematic for JIRA when attempting to load an issue with a large comment impacting performance and/or causing OOMs.

Therefore this request is for a new renderer that decides whether to use the text renderer or wiki renderer based on input size

On the Issue Navigator page https://jira.atlassian.com/issues/?jql= are three login links, which are not using the parameter link.login.url from seraph-config.xml. As a result, if you are using a SSO system and you changed the login urls in seraph, it won't reflect on the issue navigator page and users cannot login.

LoginUtils.js
{code}
    /**
     * Returns url to redirect to the current page (eg /login.jsp?os_destination=[encodedCurrentUrl]
     * @returns login url
     */
    redirectUrlToCurrent: function() {
        var url = this.currentContextRelativePath();
        return contextPath + '/login.jsp?os_destination=' + encodeURIComponent(url)
    },

    /**
     * Returns url to redirect to (eg /login.jsp?os_destination=[encodedUrl]
     * @param url url to redirect to after user has logged in
     * @returns login url
     */
    redirectUrl: function(url) {
        return contextPath + '/login.jsp?os_destination=' + encodeURIComponent(url)
    }
{code}

The main login button in the upper right corner, correctly reads the value from seraph-config.xml, but gets overwritten later by javascript.

